17/02/2011
WASHINGTON, United States -- Macedonian Prime Minister Nikola Gruevski said on Wednesday (February 16th) that the United States supports and encourages Macedonia and Greece to find a solution to their name dispute as soon as possible. 
After meeting with Vice-President Joseph Biden and Secretary of State Hillary Clinton in Washington, Gruevski said that Macedonia remains committed to resolving this issue, as it is essential for EU and NATO integration. 
(MIA, Makfax - 17/02/11)
